The paper focuses on designing a multi-party conferencing solution that can adapt to arbitrary network topologies and conditions, with an emphasis on low end-to-end delays and efficient link rate allocations. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. Additionally, the paper mentions video encoding and quality optimization, which could also place it in the Multimedia (cs.MM) category. The distributed and adaptive rate control protocol mentioned in the paper could also be relevant to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) categories. Finally, the emphasis on efficient link rate allocations and network conditions suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category.
